<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 01 at 5:14PM MDT  by NWS Glasgow</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern McCone,
northwestern Dawson and northwestern Richland Counties through 615 PM
MDT...
At 513 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Vida, or 16 miles south of Wolf Point, moving east at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Vida.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
